Package io.j4c.config

Interface ConfigMapper<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - supported mapping Java type.
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ConfigMapper<T>
    Contextual mapper of a configuration hierarchy to a Java type.

    Mappers are programmatically registered and / or automatically loaded as a services via ConfigMapperProvider SPI if not disabled.

    See Also:
    Config.Builder.addMapper(Class, ConfigMapper), Config.Builder.addMapper(Class, java.util.function.Function), Config.Builder.addMapper(io.j4c.config.spi.ConfigMapperProvider), Config.as(Class), Config.as(Class, Object), Config.asOptional(Class), Config.asList(Class), Config.asList(Class, java.util.List), Config.asOptionalList(Class), Config.map(ConfigMapper), Config.map(ConfigMapper, Object), Config.mapOptional(ConfigMapper), Config.mapList(ConfigMapper), Config.mapList(ConfigMapper, java.util.List), Config.mapOptionalList(ConfigMapper), ConfigMappers, ConfigMapperProvider, Config.Value

      T apply​(Config config)

    • Method Detail

      • apply

        T apply​(Config config)
 throws ConfigMappingException,
        MissingValueException
        Map a configuration hierarchy to a Java representation.
        Parameters:
        config - configuration node representing a configuration tree to be mapped to an instance of a Java type.
        Returns:
        node mapped to a given java type.
        Throws:
        MissingValueException - in case the configuration tree does not contain all expected sub-nodes required by the mapper implementation to provide instance of Java type.
        ConfigMappingException - in case the mapper fails to map the (existing) configuration tree represented by the supplied configuration node to an instance of a given Java type.
